President Biden and President Lula had a phone conversation, where President Biden expressed the United States' support for Brazil's democracy and the will of the Brazilian people as shown in the recent presidential election won by President Lula. President Biden condemned the violence and attack on democratic institutions. They agreed to collaborate on various issues such as climate change, economic development, and peace and security. President Biden invited President Lula to visit Washington in February for detailed discussions, and President Lula accepted the invitation.